main event: A single round object, estimated to be three feet across, was observed traveling at an estimated speed of 600 mph in Bremerton, Washington on February 11, 1956.
interesting points: The object gave out a light blue streak and seemed to emit light.
The object had a sharp, round outline and followed a straight line course to the southwest.
The sighting lasted for about 10 seconds.
The observer believed the object was possibly an aircraft due to its straight-line course, duration, and color.
The conclusion was that the sighting was possibly an aircraft.
